The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Modi ready to submit third reply 
                                                                                                                       7                                      Modi ready to submit third reply 
                      
	Mumbai: Suspended Indian Premier League (IPL) commissioner Lalit Modi is all set to submit by Tuesday his reply to the third show cause notice that the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) slapped on him for alleged irregularities in the awarding of Twenty20 Leagues theatrical rights.         
	The reply to the third notice is actively under way. We have got time till the June 15 to submit it, Modis counsel Mehmood Abdi said.         
	Modi was served the third show cause notice, which also raised questions over the awarding of the 150-second commercial slot in between balls during IPL III, by the BCCI on May 31.           (PTI)                                                                                                                 
